<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="569" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,393,525]" pageId="10" pageNumber="569">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,427,453]" pageId="10" pageNumber="569">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, J. A. &amp; Griswold, C. E. &amp; Scharff, N. &amp; Rezac, M. &amp; Szuts, T. &amp; Marhabaie, M." box="[329,546,427,454]" pageId="10" pageNumber="569" pagination="1 - 144" refId="ref6291" refString="Miller, J. A., Griswold, C. E., Scharff, N., Rezac, M., Szuts, T. &amp; Marhabaie, M. (2012) The velvet spiders: an atlas of the Eresi- dae (Arachnida, Araneae). ZooKeys, 195, 1 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 195.2342" type="journal article" year="2012">
Miller 
<emphasis box="[407,464,427,453]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="569">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
gives a diagnosis based on the ribbon-like blunt conductor, which is unique in the genus by lacking a notch (
<figureCitation box="[480,557,462,489]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–25" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1753,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,210,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[151,1436,181,1730]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20–25. Male palps of Eresus lavrosiae Mcheidze, 1997 (20–22), Eresus kollari Rossi, 1846 (23), Eresus moravicus Řezáč, 2008 (24) and Eresus walckenaeri Brullé, 1832 (25). 20. prolateral view. 21. ventral view. 22–25. retrolateral views. Scale bar = 0.5 mm (20–22). Figs 23–25 are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408077/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="569">Fig 25</figureCitation>
). Also, no terminal tooth is visible, and the lamella is well-developed, extended and overhanging the triangular-shaped tegulum (
<figureCitation box="[696,781,498,525]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–25" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1753,1777]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,210,1698]" captionTargetId="figure-20@8.[151,1436,181,1730]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20–25. Male palps of Eresus lavrosiae Mcheidze, 1997 (20–22), Eresus kollari Rossi, 1846 (23), Eresus moravicus Řezáč, 2008 (24) and Eresus walckenaeri Brullé, 1832 (25). 20. prolateral view. 21. ventral view. 22–25. retrolateral views. Scale bar = 0.5 mm (20–22). Figs 23–25 are not to scale." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408077" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408077/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="569">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
